Japanese amusement game giant Sega Enterprises Ltd.  said Thursday its consolidated pre-tax earnings plunged 62 percent from a year  earlier to 21.7 billion yen (210 million dollars) in the year to March.
The company said worldwide sales were stagnant at less than 417 billion  yen, up less than one percent from the previous year.
Sega forecast sharply higher group earnings of 44 billion yen with sales  edging up towards 420 billion yen.
